SELECT

  value1
FROM
  metric_table
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(time_column)

select count(distinct mhm.cluster_id) as "Enabled" from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhm
join organizations org on org.organization_id = mhm.organization_id
join cluster_details c on c.cluster_id = mhm.cluster_id
join node_details n on n.node_id = mhm.node_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and
n.host_name in ($HostName)

select (y.b - x.a) as "Disabled" from (select count(distinct c.cluster_id) as "b" from organizations org
join cluster_details c on c.organization_id = org.organization_id
join node_details n on n.cluster_id = c.cluster_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and
n.host_name in ($HostName)) y,
(select count(distinct mhm.cluster_id) as "a" from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhm 
join organizations org on org.organization_id = mhm.organization_id
join cluster_details c on c.cluster_id = mhm.cluster_id
join node_details n on n.node_id = mhm.node_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) ) x

select count(distinct mhm.node_id) as "Enabled" from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhm
join organizations org on org.organization_id = mhm.organization_id
join cluster_details c on c.cluster_id = mhm.cluster_id
join node_details n on n.node_id = mhm.node_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and
n.host_name in ($HostName)

select (y.b - x.a) as "Disabled" from (select count(distinct n.node_id) as "b" from organizations org
join cluster_details c on c.organization_id = org.organization_id
join node_details n on n.cluster_id = c.cluster_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and
n.host_name in ($HostName)) y,
(select count(distinct mhm.node_id) as "a" from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhm
join organizations org on org.organization_id = mhm.organization_id
join cluster_details c on c.cluster_id = mhm.cluster_id
join node_details n on n.node_id = mhm.node_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
c.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) ) x

SELECT 
COUNT(*) as "Success"
from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhmt join organizations o on o.organization_id = mhmt.organization_id
where test_name = 'SIP Signalling' and $__timeFilter(test_timestamp) and test_result = 'Success' and organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and host_name in ($HostName) and trigger_type in ($TriggerType)
and test_id in ($TestId)

select count(failure_reason), failure_reason as "Value" from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhmt join organizations o on o.organization_id = mhmt.organization_id
where failure_reason is NOT NULL and test_name = 'SIP Signalling' and $__timeFilter(test_timestamp) and test_result = 'Failed' and organization_name in ('$OrganizationName')  and cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and host_name in ($HostName) and trigger_type in ($TriggerType) and test_id in ($TestId)
group by failure_reason

test_timestamp as "time", 
CASE WHEN test_result = 'Success' THEN 1 end as "Success"
from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhmt

select mhm.test_timestamp as "Timestamp",
mhm.test_id as "Test ID",
org.organization_name as "Organization Name", 
mhm.cluster_name as "Cluster Name", 
mhm.host_name as "Host Name",
mhm.trigger_type as "Trigger Type",
mhm.test_name as "Test",
case when(mhm.test_result = 'Success') then 1 else 0 end as "Result",
mhm.failure_reason as "Failure Reason"
from media_health_monitoring_test_results mhm
join organizations org on mhm.organization_id = org.organization_id
where org.organization_name in ('$OrganizationName') and
mhm.host_name in ($HostName) and
mhm.cluster_name in ($ClusterName) and
$__timeFilter(mhm.timestamp) and
mhm.test_id in ($TestId) and
mhm.trigger_type in ($TriggerType)
order by mhm.test_timestamp, mhm.test_name
